  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "For each meta-regression model, we calculated the total heterogeneity (Q M) and the proportion of total heterogeneity explained by moderators (marginal R 2), with the function r2_ml using the orchard package 91.",
    "P values (α = 0.05) indicate whether the heterogeneity explained was significant or not 90.",
    "We created models without an intercept to test whether each level of a moderator showed evidence for senescence or improvement in ejaculate traits with age.",
    "However, for moderators with two levels, we were additionally interested in comparing effect sizes in one level to those in the other level.",
    "In such cases, we created a model with one level of the moderator as the intercept (here, a P value expressed whether one level of the moderator was different from the other level)."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "For each meta-regression model, we calculated the total heterogeneity (Q M) and the proportion of total heterogeneity explained by moderators (marginal R 2), with the function r2_ml using the orchard package 91.",
    "P values (α = 0.05) indicate whether the heterogeneity explained was significant or not 90."
  ]
